        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stewartsville, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Vinton...
Montvale...
Stewartsville...
Laymantown...
Chamblissburg...
Peaks Of Otter Recreation Area...
and Blue Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
